=\"table-link\">@Compendium[world.ddb-solvcretis-faerun-ddb-tables.Background: Criminal / Spy: Flaw]{Open RollTable Background: Criminal / Spy: Flaw}</div><p></p><h2>Criminal Contact</h2><p>You have a reliable and trustworthy contact who acts as your liaison to a network of other criminals. You know how to get messages to and from your contact, even over great distances; specifically, you know the local messengers, corrupt caravan masters, and seedy sailors who can deliver messages for you.</p><h3>Choices</h3><ul><li>Deception</li><li>Stealth</li><li>Playing Card Set</li><li>Thieves' Tools</li></ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":null,"advancement":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":null,"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"}},"flags":{"ddbimporter":{"id":8,"type":"background","entityTypeId":1669830167,"dndbeyond":{},"importId":"MLBPSZ2OFpGscfI8"},"obsidian":{"source":{"type":"background"}},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.qFBzLiY0x5XDMqky.Item.PPwnge3w6Eqag103"}},"effects":[],"img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-book-study-purple.webp","folder":null,"sort":101563,"ownership":{"default":0,"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672140189996,"modifiedTime":1672571716302,"lastModifiedBy":"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE"},"_id":"zJXkfBUGVCwc3JMV"}
{"name":"College of Lore","type":"subclass","system":{"description":{"value":"<h1>Description</h1><p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Bards of the College of Lore know something about most things, collecting bits of knowledge from sources as diverse as scholarly tomes and peasant tales. Whether singing folk ballads in taverns or elaborate compositions in royal courts, these bards use their gifts to hold audiences spellbound. When the applause dies down, the audience members might find themselves questioning everything they held to be true, from their faith in the priesthood of the local temple to their loyalty<span class=\"No-Break\"> to the king.</span></p><h1>Class Features</h1>\n\n<p><b>Bonus Proficiencies</b></p>\n<p>When you join the College of Lore at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with three skills of your choice.</p>\n\n<p><b>Cutting Words</b></p>\n<p>Also at 3rd level, you learn how to use your wit to distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others. When a creature that you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a damage roll, you can use your reaction to expend one of your uses of Bardic Inspiration, rolling a Bardic Inspiration die and subtracting the number rolled from the creature’s roll. You can choose to use this feature after the creature makes its roll, but before the DM determines whether the attack roll or ability check succeeds or fails, or before the creature deals its damage. The creature is immune if it can’t hear you or if it’s immune to being @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.w7eitkpD7QQTB6j0]{charmed}.</p>\n\n<p><b>Additional Magical Secrets</b></p>\n<p>At 6th level, you learn two spells of your choice from any class. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. The chosen spells count as bard spells for you but don’t count against the number of bard spells you know.</p>\n\n<p><b>Peerless Skill</b></p>\n<p>Starting at 14th level, when you make an ability check, you can expend one use of Bardic Inspiration. Roll a Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to your ability check. You can choose to do so after you roll the die for the ability check, but before the DM tells you whether you succeed or fail.</p>\n\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","identifier":"college-of-lore","classIdentifier":"bard","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"flags":{"ddbimporter":{"subclassDefinitionId":54940657,"id":18,"type":"class","importId":"MLBPSZ2OFpGscfI8"},"obsidian":{"source":{"type":"class","text":"College of Lore"}},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.qFBzLiY0x5XDMqky.Item.IJhAtDaGTbbqqxFT"}},"img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-book-study-runes.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672140189801,"modifiedTime":1672571719952,"lastModifiedBy":"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE"},"_id":"tNO7eEspMvP9dRLJ"}
{"name":"College of Lore","type":"subclass","system":{"description":{"value":"<h1>Description</h1><p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Bards of the College of Lore know something about most things, collecting bits of knowledge from sources as diverse as scholarly tomes and peasant tales. Whether singing folk ballads in taverns or elaborate compositions in royal courts, these bards use their gifts to hold audiences spellbound. When the applause dies down, the audience members might find themselves questioning everything they held to be true, from their faith in the priesthood of the local temple to their loyalty<span class=\"No-Break\"> to the king.</span></p><h1>Class Features</h1>\n\n<p><b>Bonus Proficiencies</b></p>\n<p>When you join the College of Lore at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with three skills of your choice.</p>\n\n<p><b>Cutting Words</b></p>\n<p>Also at 3rd level, you learn how to use your wit to distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others. When a creature that you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a damage roll, you can use your reaction to expend one of your uses of Bardic Inspiration, rolling a Bardic Inspiration die and subtracting the number rolled from the creature’s roll. You can choose to use this feature after the creature makes its roll, but before the DM determines whether the attack roll or ability check succeeds or fails, or before the creature deals its damage. The creature is immune if it can’t hear you or if it’s immune to being @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.w7eitkpD7QQTB6j0]{charmed}.</p>\n\n<p><b>Additional Magical Secrets</b></p>\n<p>At 6th level, you learn two spells of your choice from any class. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. The chosen spells count as bard spells for you but don’t count against the number of bard spells you know.</p>\n\n<p><b>Peerless Skill</b></p>\n<p>Starting at 14th level, when you make an ability check, you can expend one use of Bardic Inspiration. Roll a Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to your ability check. You can choose to do so after you roll the die for the ability check, but before the DM tells you whether you succeed or fail.</p>\n\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","identifier":"college-of-lore","classIdentifier":"bard","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"flags":{"ddbimporter":{"subclassDefinitionId":54940657,"id":18,"type":"class","importId":"MLBPSZ2OFpGscfI8"},"obsidian":{"source":{"type":"class","text":"College of Lore"}},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.qFBzLiY0x5XDMqky.Item.IJhAtDaGTbbqqxFT"}},"img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-book-study-runes.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":100782,"ownership":{"default":0,"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672140189801,"modifiedTime":1672571719970,"lastModifiedBy":"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE"},"_id":"tNO7eEspMvP9dRLJ"}
{"name":"Наемник-путешественник","type":"background","system":{"description":{"value":"<h1>Background: Наемник-путешественник</h1><p>Коренаст и крепок, ростом 180, с иссиня-черными небрежными волосами, густыми усами и бородой. Недавно стукнуло 27, но выглядит старше своих лет. Всегда молчалив и задумчив, говорит тихо, предпочитает общаться знаками. Знает, когда нужно взять, а когда - отдать. Выгоды не упустит, но не во вред другим. Родился в деревушке близ Невервинтера. Мать умерла при родах, поэтому рос с отцом. Тот был кузнецом и часто ездил с Йориком в Невервинтер на рынок, где продавал свои изделия. Йорика никогда не привлекало дело отца, но он исправно помогал ему во всем. В свободное от дел время он брал доспехи и оружие из кузни и упражнялся в фехтовании. Как-то раз к отцу Йорика приехал его старый друг Орэн, служивший наёмником в одной торговой гильдии. Он прибыл с караваном в Невервинтер и решил заглянуть к своему товарищу. Увидев тягу Йорика к оружию, он решил дать пару уроков. Движения подростка были быстры и сильны, но видна была их неумелость. Орэн, видя рвения сына своего друга, предложил тому взять Йорика в ученики. Так началась его новая жизнь, полная опасностей и приключений. Многое произошло за то время. Орэн стал вторым отцом Йорику. Он обучал его как оружию, так и рассказывал при мир вокруг них. Йорик возмужал и стал отлично владеть как мечом, так щитом, сделанным для него отцом. Окованный тусклой сталью, потрепанный во многих боях, наполовину черный - наполовину белый. В одном из походов они везли особо ценный груз во Врата Балдура. На их несчастье, впереди их ждала крупная засада. Завязался ожесточенный бой. Груз был спасен, но не все его защитники. Среди тел разбойников лежало одно. Оно улыбалось Йорику кровавой улыбкой. Взгляд потух и на том был конец Орэна. Стоя перед керном своего второго отца, Йорик осознал, что все еще не знает, чего жаждет и к чему стремится. Он знал одно: в его левой руке - щит родного отца, а в правой - меч названного. Теперь он знал, как огромен мир, и сколько всего еще ему предстоит познать. Проведя мечем в воздухе от керна к звездному небу, он тихо произнес: \"Я найду свой путь\".\nЗавершив сопровождение груза, он решил взять перерыв и все обдумать. Он понял, что был в Вотердипе только мельком, хотя этот город так расхваливал Орэн. Основательно отдохнув и пережив утрату, он отправился в путь, полный решимости исследовать все земли Фаеруна.</p><h2>Folk Hero</h2><p>You come from a humble social rank, but you are destined for so much more. Already the people of your home village regard you as their champion, and your destiny calls you to stand against the tyrants and monsters that threaten the common folk everywhere.</p><h3>Rustic Hospitality</h3><p>Since you come from the ranks of the common folk, you fit in among them with ease. You can find a place to hide, rest, or recuperate among other commoners, unless you have shown yourself to be a danger to them. They will shield you from the law or anyone else searching for you, though they will not risk their lives for you.</p><h3>Choices</h3><ul></ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules","advancement":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":null,"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"}},"flags":{"ddbimporter":{"id":9,"type":"background","entityTypeId":1669830167,"dndbeyond":{},"importId":"o9FHvJnYS2jAgBI5"},"obsidian":{"source":{"type":"background"}},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.2j3MdvwEzwZ0Ccps.Item.veXu9KBYebfm0Sah"}},"img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-book-study-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671571778753,"modifiedTime":1672572049140,"lastModifiedBy":"8pEKuxhCYVCDuXDE"},"_id":"RoZoQHXDAu0oBN6r"}
